cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and morphological inflection. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a neural architecture for the task. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper deals with automated generation of inflected forms. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is relevant as the paper proposes a neural architecture. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with graphical features of characters.
